#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
keyferry — 1Password ⇄ Bitwarden/Vaultwarden credential ferry  v1.0.0
Intelligently migrate and sync passwords between 1Password and Bitwarden/Vaultwarden,
with vault→collection mapping, content-aware deduplication, and timestamp-aware delta syncing.

Architecture:
    source adapter (1pux file | op live | bw live)
        → normalized item model + content signature
        → vault/state mapping resolver (private vs shared)
        → dedup / delta engine (update when source is newer; --overwrite forces all)
        → sink adapter (bw serve fast-path | op item create)

Usage:
    keyferry doctor                 Check op/bw CLIs, auth, versions
    keyferry status                 Show both sides: vaults, collections, counts
    keyferry plan                   Dry-run: what would be created / skipped (no writes)
    keyferry plan --from X --to Y   Dry-run preview (no writes)
    keyferry sync --from X --to Y   Ferry credentials (X/Y = 1password | bitwarden | file.1pux)
    keyferry map                    Interactively edit the vault→collection mapping
    keyferry config get/set/list    Manage configuration

Dependencies:
    pip install rich requests readchar      (op + bw CLIs installed separately)
"""

